In <940116.74076.ROY_GRIFFIN@delphi.com> ROY_GRIFFIN@delphi.com writes:
>I am designing some security into a product that will be sold in Mexico.
>I need a crypto algorithm that is exportable...

Thought I'd point out that if hardware crypto is OK, IBM makes crypto
products with an exportable algorithm.  We have a smart card, PC card,
RS/6000 card, and mainframe unit that use CDMF, the "Commercial Data
Masking Facility".  CDMF is an algorithm with 40-bit strength, and which
is exportable.

    Todd Arnold
